AI-driven voice and chat interviews for customers and leads in 30+ languages
Automated CRM-integrated Win/Loss interviews and analysis
UX and product research with built-in analytics
Customizable, purpose-specific research templates
Real-time dashboards and actionable summary reports
Effortless integration your internal customer tooling (CRM, support platforms, etc.)
Why Propane?
Reduce research costs by over 90%, or run over 10x the amount of research at similar cost levels
Capture more candid, in-depth customer feedback
Fully embed Propane into your existing customer experiences
Automatically reward research participants with custom incentives
Get insights fast enough to drive business decisions instantly
Empower product, GTM, and research teams to operate at scale
Top startups and global companies use Propane to power their customer intelligence, drive product market fit, reduce churn, and fuel continuous growth.
Ideal for: Product teams, Revenue leaders, UX researchers, Customer success, Growth and Marketing teams, and anyone wanting to understand customers and leads—fast, accurately, and at scale.

name: AI Flow Chat
businessDescription:
No-code workflow tool for automating and chaining AI prompts. 

Features a drag-and-drop builder, model flexibility, one-click sharing as apps, and reusable automation templates. 

Popular among writers, analysts, and creators for drastically reducing time of AI tasks.
longBusinessDescription:
AI Flow Chat is a no-code automation platform that turns repetitive AI conversations into reusable, shareable apps. With its drag-and-drop visual builder, teams can design end-to-end workflows that chain multiple prompt, known as prompt chaining, to break complex work into clear reliable steps.  
Visual AI Flow Builder
– Build multi-step prompt chains without writing code.
– Insert conditional branches, loops, and role-based prompts for advanced logic.  
Programmatic Prompting
– Parameterize prompts with variables pulled from user input, databases, or APIs.
– Dynamically generate or refine prompts at runtime for personalized, context-aware output.  
Model Flexibility
– Mix fast, standard, and premium LLMs in the same flow to balance cost and quality.  
One-Click Deployment
– Publish any prompt chain as a branded, shareable web app—public or private—in seconds.  
Prompt chaining lets marketers, writers, analysts, and creators decompose work into atomic steps (e.g., extract → analyze → generate → summarize)

name: DevOps Agent
businessDescription:
DevOps Agent is an AI-powered co-pilot that automates your entire deployment lifecycle—from code to production and beyond. Connect your GitHub, GitLab or Bitbucket repository and let our AI:

- Analyze & Infer your stack: automatically detect languages, frameworks and dependencies.
- Generate Infrastructure: create production-ready Dockerfiles, Kubernetes and Helm manifests tailored to your application.
- One-Click Deploy: push to AWS, GCP, Azure, DigitalOcean, Linode and more without writing a single configuration file.
- ChatOps Interface: manage deployments, scaling, rollbacks and security scans through natural-language commands in Slack, Teams or your terminal.
- Real-Time Insights: get live dashboards for performance metrics, cost forecasting and compliance checks.
- Continuous Management: automatically detect configuration drift, apply safe rollbacks, optimize resource utilization and enforce policy guardrails.

Built for startups and scale-ups that need production-grade reliability at startup velocity, DevOps Agent removes manual complexity, shrinks release cycles to minutes, and empowers every team member—no DevOps expertise required. Sign up for our early beta at [https://devopsagent.dev](https://devopsagent.dev/) and start deploying smarter, faster, automatically.
longBusinessDescription:
DevOps Agent is an AI‑powered platform that turns the chaos of modern infrastructure into a one‑click, production‑ready workflow. Built on proven giants—GitHub, GitLab, Kubernetes, Docker, Terraform, AWS, GCP, Azure and more—we don’t replace your favorite tools; we orchestrate them. Our agent auto‑scans every repository, understands its languages and dependencies, then generates optimized Docker images, Kubernetes/Helm manifests or Terraform stacks in seconds. One chat command later, those resources are live in any cloud —complete with automated rollbacks, cost forecasts, performance dashboards and continuous security scans.
Where legacy DevOps pipelines struggle with tool‑chain sprawl, hidden costs and brittle YAML, DevOps Agent delivers:
AI‑driven acceleration – code‑to‑production in minutes, not days.
ChatOps simplicity – deploy, scale or roll back from Slack, Teams or CLI using plain English.
Zero‑touch observability – instant CPU, latency and budget insights without manual exporters.
Built‑in security & compliance – continuous CVE scanning, least‑privilege IAM and SOC2/GDPR guardrails.
Autonomous optimisation – the agent detects drift, right‑sizes resources and patches infra before issues hit customers.
Early adopters report a 50× jump in deployment frequency, 99 % faster release times and up to 60 % reduction in monthly cloud spend—all while shrinking dedicated DevOps headcount. By automating the heavy lifting, teams reclaim precious engineering cycles to build features, delight users and outpace competitors.
We’re inviting a limited number of startups and scale‑ups into our Early Access Program. Members receive priority onboarding, founder‑level support and the chance to steer our roadmap. Join the waiting list today and experience how AI can transform “deploy anxiety” into quiet, reliable automation—so your company can focus on innovation instead of infrastructure.

name: Velatir
businessDescription:
At Velatir, we believe that the future of artificial intelligence is built on a foundation of trust, transparency, and accountability. Our mission is to empower businesses with the tools they need to integrate human judgment into their AI systems, ensuring that technology complements—not replaces—human oversight.

Who We Are
Velatir was founded with a clear vision: to bridge the gap between cutting-edge AI innovation and responsible governance. We recognize that while AI has the potential to transform industries, its decisions can sometimes carry significant consequences. That’s why we’ve designed solutions that prioritize human-centric oversight, balancing the power of automation with the critical insights only people can provide.

What We Do
Velatir offers a comprehensive suite of tools that enable businesses to seamlessly incorporate human oversight into their AI-powered workflows. Our solutions are designed to help organizations make better, safer, and more informed decisions, while ensuring compliance with evolving regulations such as the EU AI Act.
longBusinessDescription:
Our Key Features
	•	Human-in-the-Loop SDK: A lightweight, developer-friendly SDK that flags critical functions for human approval before execution.
	•	Approval Dashboard: A centralized interface for real-time decision monitoring, featuring rich data insights and notifications.
	•	Historical Decision Automation: Automates low-risk decisions based on historical patterns, with full transparency into why decisions are made.
	•	Compliance & Reporting Tools: Built-in tools aligned with Article 14 of the EU AI Act, ensuring every decision is auditable and traceable.
	•	Customizable Oversight Parameters: Tailored triggers and thresholds for oversight based on business-specific needs.
	•	AI Feedback Loop: Refines AI models by integrating human feedback to detect and mitigate biases.
	•	Seamless Integration: API-first design with support for popular frameworks and AI models for easy deployment.
Why Choose Velatir?
	•	Compliance-Driven by Design: We make regulatory adherence effortless, keeping your business aligned with legal and ethical standards.
	•	Trust and Transparency: Reduce risks and build confidence by ensuring human oversight for critical decisions.
	•	Scalable Automation: Transition to efficient, low-risk automation while maintaining full control.
	•	Cross-Industry Adaptability: Our solutions fit industries where high-stakes decisions are paramount, including healthcare, finance, and e-commerce.
	•	Plug-and-Play Simplicity: Get started quickly with minimal integration effort and intuitive tools.
	•	Future-Proof AI Governance: Stay ahead of evolving AI regulations and governance requirements.
Our Vision
We envision a world where AI operates responsibly, transparently, and collaboratively with humans. With Velatir, businesses don’t have to choose between innovation and accountability—they can achieve both.
Velatir – Empowering AI with Human Judgment: Oversight You Can Trust.

name: ATTO 3D
businessDescription: ATTO3D offers versatile solutions for micro- and nanoscale fabrication at an affordable cost, without having to compromise on the quality. Through complex optics, high-end nano-positioners, and inventive designs, ATTO3D have brought the conventional photolithography system out of the clean-room and made it available as an easily accessible service. Enjoy the power of state-of-the-art nanotechnology on demand.
longBusinessDescription: ATTO3D offers versatile solutions for micro- and nanoscale fabrication at an affordable cost, without having to compromise on the quality. Through complex optics, high-end nano-positioners, and inventive designs, ATTO3D have brought the conventional photolithography system out of the clean-room and made it available as an easily accessible service. Enjoy the power of state-of-the-art nanotechnology on demand. The idea of ATTO3D started at IDUN center of excellence at Technical University of Denmark, where the founders were challenged by a need to have local production of complex and versatile micro-containers for research purposes for the institute. Through hacking of complex but easily available optics devices, an idea took form. Using this affordable device featuring different wavelengths to cross-link photopolymers (also called resins), molding of simple structures in micro-scale resolution is possible. The design was intended to save both time and money, making an affordable in-house system with high versatility, allowing for quick prototyping in normal lab conditions. After intensive testing and optimization, a system capable of printing micro-and nanostructures in a cm-volume came to life. Knowing the capability and flexibility of the system, it was thought to be an idea too good not to bring to the world, and the endeavors of creating ATTO3D was started.

name: PassionClass
businessDescription: The AirBNB for classes.  Learn or teach anything, with real people and live class.
longBusinessDescription:
PassionClass is the most advanced new marketplace to learn anything online.  It’s like AirBNB, but for classes: from languages to baking, people can share what they know most about.  We offer live classes taught by real people, where people teach a subject because they care and know a lot about it.  On PassionClass, years of experience matter more than almost anything else.  
PassionClass is truly the best place on earth to learn a language.  Duolingo sounds great, but do you know anyone who’s actually learned to speak from an app?  You need classes, group energy, and human connection to get immersed in a language- an opportunity to come and share and exchange and experience, which is what language is truly about.  Our platform fosters this immersive experience, where learners benefit from the dynamic energy of group classes and forge meaningful human connections essential for language proficiency. Yet we offer this for a fraction of the cost of a university, plus, best of all: no grades.  Languages are back to being fun, and PassionClass is more than just learning; it's a platform for sharing, exchanging, and experiencing the essence of language.  �
PassionClass is also the best place on the internet to learn new skills.  Want to learn to bake?  Do it here.  Want to learn an instrument?  Get started right away.  Want to share the way you became a chess grandmaster?  On PassionClass, you can use your creativity to teach what you’re most passionate about.  The collaborative nature of our classes not only enhances learning but also makes it a more socially enriching experience- while also saving you money.
PassionClass is also a leading platform in the realm of creative arts, providing an unmatched opportunity for individuals to explore and cultivate their artistic talents. Whether aspiring painters, musicians, or writers, PassionClass offers a vibrant space where creators can hone their craft under the guidance of experienced instructors. Group classes in creative arts foster a supportive environment where learners can receive feedback, collaborate with peers, and draw inspiration from diverse perspectives. By combining passion with expertise, PassionClass empowers individuals to unleash their creativity, express themselves authentically, and embark on a transformative journey of artistic discovery. 
But perhaps the most valuable aspect of PassionClass is the sense of community it fosters. Learning is inherently social, and our platform provides a space for like-minded individuals to connect, collaborate, and support each other.  PassionClass is where you'll find your group: if they’re in a class because they care, then you share interests and maybe a natural connection.
A personal tutor can cost $25, $50, $100 or more per hour.  By sharing the cost of instruction on PassionClass, individuals can access high-quality learning experiences at a fraction of the price they would pay for one-on-one sessions, while teachers make real money. Plus, reviews of classes let you know whether a class is good or great before you book.  This efficient allocation of resources enables PassionClass to offer a wider variety of courses while keeping classes affordable. Additionally, group environments foster peer interaction and collaborative learning, enhancing the overall educational experience. In essence, group classes at PassionClass make quality education accessible to a broader audience, promoting lifelong learning and personal development.

name: Clean Matter Aps
businessDescription:
Clean Matter Aps is a pioneering Danish company specializing in wastewater treatment. Our flagship technology, Power-to-P, effectively recovers Phosphorus from Sewage Sludge Incineration Ash. This technology, patented by the Technical University of Denmark, has been further refined by Clean Matter Aps in collaboration with Biofos, Denmark’s premier wastewater utility responsible for the Copenhagen metropolitan area, and Kompetenzzentrum Wasser Berlin (KWB), a renowned non-profit German water research center.


Power-to-P Technology - A Glimpse:
Our proprietary electrodialysis process, Power-to-P, leverages electrical power and water to extract Phosphorus from Sewage Sludge Incineration Ash. Central to this process is the transference of ions between selective membranes, driven by an electric potential. This allows for efficient Phosphorus recovery. Notably, the process is environmentally sustainable, using only power and water and emitting no harmful gases. The outcome is a pristine, industrial-grade Phosphoric Acid, devoid of contaminants, primed for direct use as a compound in fertilizer production. Concurrently, the remaining mineral fraction, free from harmful substances, is suitable for cement aggregate use.
longBusinessDescription:

Many feel disconnected even more now due to what’s going on in the world since last year. Also, the pandemic has resulted in distancing oneself from the friends that were not so close to begin with (but perhaps wanted to become closer). 

All in all, people need effortless access to true connections with friends through real experiences.

You need not be worried, JOYN is here! We are an app helping you share free time plans with your friends, similar to how you share images on Instagram. Post and share anything from just going for a spontaneous walk or after-work drinks to a road trip across the world. It will show up on your friends’ feeds and likewise you’ll see your friends’ plans. Nice, right?

We take online connections beyond sharing superficial social media posts for likes. JOYN is for connecting with friends on another level. We want you to put the phone down; Post a plan and take it to real life to make true memories with friends and add acquaintances to easily plan with them to turn them into close friends.

User journey would look like this: 1) You can add friends to your friend circle. See their profiles with descriptions and plans. 2) Your home feed. See all your friends’ plans at once, what they are up to. 3) You can create plans. Post whatever you are up to (or if you have nothing to do, post that as well), it will show on your friends’ feeds.

Available worldwide for Android and iOS.

The platform's capabilities are extensive, ranging from inventory management and e-commerce solutions to customer relationship management and data analytics. Each feature is thoughtfully designed to work in harmony, providing a holistic solution that addresses every facet of business operation. Whether it's managing supply chains, processing orders, or gaining insights from customer data, Selldone offers a unified solution that simplifies complexity and drives efficiency.
In the spirit of the engaging narratives found in Walter Isaacson's books, Selldone's story is one of innovation, dedication, and a relentless pursuit of excellence. The team behind Selldone comprises industry experts and visionary thinkers, all united by a common goal: to empower businesses to achieve more with less. Through continuous improvement and a customer-centric approach, Selldone is not just a platform but a partner in growth, adapting and evolving to meet the changing needs of businesses.
In a marketplace where change is the only constant, We stand out as a beacon of stability and innovation. Its comprehensive suite of tools and intuitive design ensures that businesses can focus on what they do best, confident in the knowledge that their operations are supported by a robust and reliable system. With Selldone, the future of business management is not just about keeping up; it's about staying ahead.

name: Orderly
businessDescription: Orderly removes all the hassle of trading used quality items between individuals. To succeed we have developed a tech infused service chain designed to keep costs super low for handling individual items while giving the user the best possible experience. We collect the seller’s goods, take high quality product shots, store and present the items automatically on the main online markets (DBA, Google Shopping, Gul&Gratis etc..). Buyers can shop all they need in a single shipment rather than visiting multiple sellers. It gives both sellers and buyers an attractive shopping experience that is on par with new sales. We actually made it fun to tidy up your home!
longBusinessDescription:
Today trading used quality items between private individuals is a hassle. Sellers need to take photos, make descriptions, haggle with buyers and meet them on their doorsteps. Buyers too must haggle with sellers, buy stuff based on low quality images and visit several sellers when buying used goods. In addition, there are challenges with trust, cheating, warranty and returns. The result is that only 47% of the Danes bothered to sell anything on an online market in 2020 (Genbrugsindekset 2021). Quality items with many years of use left in them ends up in basements, ceilings and storage services and are eventually thrown out. That is a fundamental and unnecessary waste in a society struggling with climate change. 
A used item is unique, it has an individual story. You cannot sell it on a generic product ad. The photo and description must be of the individual item. New items are on the contrary interchangeable. Sellers can sell thousands of identical items on the same product ad. This has up until now made the handling and selling of used single items at scale prohibitively expensive.
Meet Orderly. Orderly is a new service that removes all the hassle of trading used quality items. We pick up the seller’s goods, take high quality product shots, store and present the items automatically on the dominating online markets (DBA, Google Shopping etc..). Buyers can buy all they need in a single shipment rather than visiting multiple sellers. It gives both sellers and buyers an attractive shopping experience that is on par with new sales. Traditional product shots and descriptions often takes hours per product, a process only feasible for interchangeable goods. By integrating tech services which were not available five years ago, Orderly has optimized the process by a factor x100 which mean that we can take professional shots and describe items in seconds rather than hours. We have also fully integrated the many individual steps of the sales process into a semi-automated flow to keep costs low. This has suddenly made hassle-free exchange of quality stuff a sound business opportunity while contributing at scale to a more circular economy. 
The technologies behind our service include 1) a custom built and automated professional photo studio, 3) automatic photo enhancement and cropping, 4) automatic tagging and property identification through image recognition, 5) speech recognition and 6) an integrated warehouse solution with fast in/out service.

name: CaseLab
businessDescription: CaseLab is the first task and project management tool on the market tailored for IT business transformations (ERP, CRM, WEB, BI). It brings all project work into one tool, so you have your coding in DevOps/Jira and EVERYTHING else in CaseLab - plans, tasks, history, estimates, time, customer dialogue, documentation. One tool to replace all the others your teams run projects in today (Excel, Outlook, SharePoint, MS Project). With our pre-delivered ERP/project templates it is much easier to run efficient and smooth projects. Create projects based on pre-setup, all including templates with best practice models, where all phases and tasks are ready to go. We call it shake and bake projects. Simply select a project start date and the system does all the planning for you. Easy, no matter your or your team's experience. You can also create and maintain your own project templates, so your delivery methods get better based on learnings for each project you run. WHY DOES THE ERP WORLD NEED ANOTHER PROJECT MANAGEMENT TOOL? When we worked as project managers and consultants, we spent a really long time forcing DevOps to fit in with fx D365, AX or SAP implementations. And we had to give up every time and realize that we could not set up and manage our projects in it, while people still ran most of the project work outside the system. We also realized that it is not a change management problem that our consultants and client users did not use the system - it was simply because it was built for something completely different than running ERP projects. We could not bear to face another long and painful attempt to get our consultants and clients to use DevOps, which in all cases always ended with each person having an individual process for solving their tasks (Excel, Outlook, SharePoint).

Our sales campaign was launched in June 2021. The current #NoFever market consists of businesses, organisations, and public institutions in Denmark, however, we intend to acquire a target market in other countries in the nearest future.  Significantly, #NoFever has a perspective of a long-term product life after the pandemic, ensuring security entry system: scanning tickets, performing identity validation and temperature checks, guiding, etc.
The core team consists of Co-founder & CEO Jevgenijs Galaktionovs, Co-founder & CTO Hugo Markoff and Co-founder & CXO Andreas Hein Hoffmann. Together we encompass experience in fields such as artificial intelligence, machine learning, programming, sensors, electronics, product design, kinematics, dynamics, computer vision, neural networks, complex mobile robotics, and user experience. Considering our knowledge and background, the future plan entails development of many more innovative robotic solutions.

Niirly works on four planes:
Incognito - this is the default mode. You are invisible to others but can still enjoy the full app - you first become visible when you decide to engage in activities and conversations
Stories - where you express yourself by us of the in-app camera to post short video stories or post pictures that disappears after 48 hours

Nicolai Busekist – Partner - CTO
Nicolai holds an BSc Engineering Degree in Electronics and Programming and has for more than 25 years been a consultant for the biggest companies in Denmark. He has extensive experience in managing and controlling large scale IT operations from early startups to major complex systems. He has also been involved working with offshore IT teams for many years. Further Nicolai has more than 20 years of programming experience.
On the side Nicolai has founded a number of startups.
I 2006 Nicolai co-founded Copenhagen Driving Range – a professional Golf Driving Range - in Nordhavn, Center of Copenhagen, with his partner Martin Andersen. Nicolai later sold his part to his partner.
In 2008 Nicolai founded Mejuba, a photo and video sharing site that contented for 20 Most Promising IT Startup in Denmark in 2010. 
Charlotte Skovmand – Partner - CEO
Educated as Master of Science in Economics and Business Administration, Charlotte has been working for more than 20 years as a business and management consultant. Charlotte is a highly experienced innovator and entrepreneur with deep knowledge in all aspects of business formation and has started a number of startups within a wide range of industries, including
HOMESTYLING – a company that provides staging of homes for sales.
Sundhedsrådgivningen - which offers counseling and healthcare services within dieting, smoking, alcohol and exercise and
booking.dk, which was sold to booking.com, one of the biggest online hotel booking companies worldwide.
Thus Charlotte has a solid knowledge of managing a startup and is furthermore an effective communicator. Her experience has taught her to maintain the stamina to keep going when things get tough as the often do in a startup. longBusinessDescription:
Travel Kollekt is an “on demand” inspiration platform and personal publishing tool. We give travellers authorship of their journeys, allowing them to be present, providing space for more personal contact and meaningful interaction. We believe in individuality and the wisdom of the crowds. So we also want to prove that planning, sustainable travel, and serendipity can go hand in hand.
We are bringing paper and books back into the traveling experience. We have taken it upon ourselves to liberate content from its current constrained formats and distracting social media. Instead, we let you curate inspiration & expert content to create personal travel guides. We remain digital only to help you to enjoy the distinct experience of a printed book. We do this because memories in books have the power to last.
• Travel Kollekt takes personal travel planning to a whole new level. It is the only tool that allows travellers from all over the world to organize information and create personalized travel guide books.
• Our mission: empower people to take authorship of their journey to create the best memories. We want to remind travellers that personal choices matter!
• Travel Kollekt was born from a personal need. After a trip to Myanmar, Louise realized that the time invested in pre-trip research has a direct impact on the quality of later memories. That is, travel time may be short, but good planning helps create memories that will last forever. So why not to create a tool that assists organize the mess of the planning process and that helps celebrate the research instead?
• Focuses on a growing audience of travellers looking for personalization, Travel Kollekt is the ideal partner for those who celebrate planning with great joy. Travel Kollekt empower informed travellers!
• The tool combines different technologies into a single platform, allowing users to store travel information; scraping content from websites; organizing data within a map; customize guides through the book editor. We have created a solution that celebrates the inspiration and planning process with beautiful design, aesthetics, simplicity, and technology.
• Travel Kollekt offers the natural and most handy way to organize content. We provide an easy template that automatically translates all texts, images, maps, addresses, and links into a fixed grid and then generate a guide book.
• The "kollekts" fits with most languages in the world, allowing users to scrape content from any source while retaining the original characters.
• Travel Kollekt is building a global database of professional writing to offer to travellers that want to go deeper and understand a destination from a more responsible and contemporary perspective.
• When we encourage people to go deep in their research, we are creating a new landscape for tourism, a responsible way of thinking. That is why we are aligned with The Global Code of Ethics for Tourism. The World Tourism Organization (UNWTO) states that to be a responsible traveller, you should "Learn as much as possible about your destination and take time to understand the customs, norms, and traditions."
• We provide curated city guides and essays written by local authors and partners from more than five countries (so far). We think that people and companies who dedicate their time and knowledge to help other travellers should be rewarded, so the collaboration is done with a revenue share that always favors
the creators and authors – precisely the way it should be. Thus, any user can purchase the content, directly contributing to more responsible tourism.
• We work to offer insights and information that will help sustainability in tourism to become a regular part of any travel experience.

businessDescription:

We call it an assembly line for omnichannel marketing, because 'Hey' it should be easier to be creative and to work across silos.
tags: martech solution, version-control system, marketing git hub,
longBusinessDescription:
Marketing is in the midst of another digital era: With hundreds of channels, services and endless communication opportunities, the daily hunt for customers and dialogue has been pushed into a hectic silo-divided everyday life. Where internal departments are working with their own focus on content and objectives, knowledge sharing across other departments will only take place at meetings or on special occasions.
Pressure on marketing departments is increasing, inevitably causing stress, frustration and wastage of resources. An increased pressure that calls for a digital transformation and a new work structure.
Today, more than half of marketing executives work to decentralize their efforts to meet a digital transformation and achieve the company's growth goals. A trend that will mean more uncoordinated efforts and new types of employment going forward. Therefore, between marketing operators and analysts, agile coaches and MarTech managers are hired into the marketing departments. Brand new features in an otherwise traditional marketing team that will help strengthen and manage the agile and digital efforts of the future.
To guide the new approach in marketing, HeyLouise will develop a solution that supports the marketing department in a digital hectic everyday life. Elevate the high demands of individual campaigns and provide insight across channels. We develop a marketing hub that is inspired by an agile development process taken from the daily life of the programmer and the agile project manager. GitHub is an indispensable tool for managing processes and versions.
Value
creation By using artificial intelligence and data, we will eliminate some of the stresses that daily weigh marketing and create inefficient processes. Specifically, we want to:
Minimize time to recover materials - new and old
Minimize uncoordinated feedback and versions of materials
Optimize collaboration in marketing and across teams to support the digital transformation
Optimize on creativity and channel utilization
Optimize on material recycling and resources
History and status
10 years of experience in marketing with campaigns, service, communication has created the idea. Mistakes occur daily during a hectic everyday life, where collaboration with many stakeholders stresses and confuses. Today, the problem has only worsened. 68% of marketing people still lack that overview. 80% struggle with cross-sector collaboration and over $ 115 billion is spent each year on systems that often share the team.
was impossible to obtain from graphic designers and contributors. Not because they didn't want to, but because it was difficult and time-consuming to find the right version when the files were named “final.final.v.2.2016.FIANAL” in the last minutes.
The project originates from an everyday problem in every marketing department. Every day, marketing department employees struggle to keep up with developments. To launch campaigns and to keep up with customers. Service, communication and presence are essential for a company that needs to market itself well. Often, the division of labor is divided between departments, systems and freelancers, which makes coordination demanding and difficult. And because it is difficult in a busy day to get the threads together, you work in silos to secure yourself and your own team.
With HeyLouise we will change that.

name: Mapscaping
businessDescription:
MAPSCAPING.COM - MAPS WITH A STORY

We love natural landscapes and we love maps!. Maps are perhaps as fundamental to society as language and the written word. Maps tell stories by recording information, about the location and spatial characteristics of the natural world and of society and culture. There is just something fascinating about looking at a landscape and imagining the processes that have shaped it.  Maps are magical, they represent the past, the present and hint at the possibilities for the future.


How we make our designs

Our topographic map designs are based on elevation data. Each of our designs is the result of hundreds of millions of elevation measurements. These measurements are then filtered into a single elevation measurement for every 30 square meters or 98 square feet. Because the geographic location of each elevation measurement is known it can be displayed as a highly-detailed map.


What we do

Our high-resolution maps are made from real data. We process the data, add the colors and let nature do the rest. The result is a beautifully detailed image, 126-megapixel image of a landscape stripped of vegetation, and man-made objects. We use two different design styles to highlight the natural topography of a landscape

businessDescription: We bring the power of advanced analytics to the maritime bunkering segment. We offer two products: Bunker Planner for Bunker Buyers, BargeTracker for (physical) Bunker Suppliers. We consider a wide range of operational constraints, such as tank capacities, margin requirements, commingling constraints, SECAs, fuel quarantines, and many others. Using sophisticated optimization algorithms, our application crunches through hundreds of alternative bunkering plans, uncovering thousands of dollars in potential savings. Contact us today to arrange a pilot evaluation for your fleet. BargeTracker is a web based analytical IT tool for bunker suppliers, giving them an overview of their market. What is the current status of supply, demand and competition? Answering this based on solid facts, gives a bunker trader the critical insight to optimize the price for a request for quotation, plan stock levels and ultimately improve their company's bottom line. Our tool currently tracks barge activity in ARA, Hamburg, St Petersburg, Piraeus, and Genoa. Request a free trial to explore the functionality of this unique product. The team behind BunkerMetric have deep expertise in, data analysis, optimization, AIS data, and software development and are working in a fast-paced agile fashion with constant focus of bringing value to our clients. Their concept is no cure no pay, as they want it to be risk free for tenants to get help, however, their win-rate is 98%.

DIGURA's digital mindset makes them stand out in the legal industry. They have made it convenient for tenants, and tenants no longer have to deal with expensive contingents and lawyer bills to get help. longBusinessDescription:
A new era is on the rise. 
The world is changing, and a new era is emerging: The data era. For restaurants to be successful today,
it’s crucial to have access to insights about their guests and business to stay relevant and continuously
provide every guest with a personalised experience, making them come back and share the experience
with their friends and family. But collecting these insights is not easy, and it’s more challenging to run a
restaurant than ever before.
No way of connecting the dots. 
For too long restaurants have been using multiple systems which cannot integrate to manage their daily
operations — leaving restaurants worldwide with a slow workflow and no way to access, collect and make
use of data about their guests and business. Without this data restaurants are forced to guess their way forward, leaving money on the table every day, struggling to optimise performance, upsell to guests and build repeat business.
Until now...
Introducing Guest Experience Management.
Superb’s Guest Experience Management platform (GXM) gathers all the tools to run a restaurant — in one place.
GXM frees up time and provides restaurant teams worldwide with a convenient workflow while collecting data to take control of the business and give every guest a personalised experience, build relationships and increase
revenue — The key to a successful restaurant.
Leading restaurants in 100+ cities worldwide use Superb to free up time and work smarter by gathering all their tools in one platform while collecting insights to give every guest a personalised experience, build relationships and increase revenue.

longBusinessDescription:
SoilSense is an agro-technology company that works to solve one of the grandest climate challenges of this century - water scarcity. We are driven by the ambition of making a real difference in the world. Today, more than 70% of all available freshwater is used for watering crops. This puts farming at the center of attention if we are to solve theglobal challenge of water scarcity.
SoilSense offers an affordable soil sensor and software solution that helps farmers optimize the growth of their crops, by intelligently recommending when and where to water. SoilSense-farmers reduce water usage and increase their yield.

Loss-of-function mutations in PCSK9 are causally linked to hypocholesterolemia and confer protection against heart disease, while gain-of-function mutations have been found to cause hypercholesterolemia and an increased risk of heart disease. Modulating the interaction of PCSK9 with the LDL receptor is a therapeutically validated strategy for lowering blood LDL cholesterol and the risk of heart disease.

introDus is a mobile, cloud-based pre and onboarding solution which enables companies to create custom onboarding content to share online with new hires, with the aim of improving employee time to performance and making them feel part of the team from day one.

The content composer allows organizations to create their own content containing all the information both new and existing employees need to know. The media library can handle any kind of file such as Powerpoint, Word, PDF, Excel, video and audio, alongside an easy to sort feature.

Quizzes help ensure employees understand the important findings, and feel safe, from day one. Users can take tests on the company’s history, values and leadership practices, study the handbook rules and learn about the products, services and processes of the company.

Track and follow employee progress and provide surveys to get valuable feedback on the onboarding process for improvements. Users can also access stats that show how well employees are doing in their pre & onboarding runs. Organizations can engage with employees via SMS, push and email to keep employees up to date on pre and onboarding information.

name: Duuoo.io
businessDescription:
The performance review has remained fundamentally unchanged for decades. At Duuoo, we’re on a mission to change that. We’re committed to improving performance management by using cutting edge technology and purposeful design to put people at the center of it.

Duuoo is a performance management platform for the 21st century: seamlessly integrated 1-on-1s, development reviews, 360º feedback & OKR/goal tracking.

Our cloud-based software, devised for forward-thinking organizations, is easy to implement, intuitive to use and helps leaders drive high-performing and engaged teams.

Want to learn more? Feel free to reach out to us at [email protected]
longBusinessDescription:
At Duuoo, we’re on a mission to change corporate culture and lead it into the future.
Our platform empowers managers to be great leaders and meet the new generations’ desire for more recognition, involvement and development. It brings employees and managers closer together by facilitating their cooperation through continuous, constructive and forward-looking dialogues.
When first developing our software, it was abundantly clear to us that while there is much talk in the corporate world about good leadership and it’s crucial importance in every aspect of business, surprisingly little is done to support managers in being good leaders. It’s for that reason that we created Duuoo with the goal of giving every manager the tools they need to be a great leader.
With Duuoo, companies become the owner of a product that forges strong professional relationships through meaningful conversation, a product that allows them to create a true coaching culture in their organization. It’s a tremendous help to the time-pressed leader.
To be blunt, the annual review is dead. And we say good riddance. Setting aside time for only one serious talk about performance and development over the course of a year is absolutely inadequate, and a sure way to create disengaged, unmotivated and unhappy employees.
Today’s employees need active guidance, support, coaching and clear goals that align with their individual purpose. They need a deeply committed leader. The sad truth is, however, that many managers have neither the time, nor the training, nor the tools necessary to make this commitment. That’s where Duuoo comes in. We automate the admin of scheduling meetings and sending out calendar invites, provide helpful and timely notification, supply them with content and learnings to inspire meaningful conversation, and give them an overview of everything happening with their team at a glance.
Contemporary studies show us that people have a deep desire for purpose in their job, just as in their life. They crave meaning; and they look for their leader to help them find it. It’s a big job, no doubt about it, but with the right tools, we truly believe every manager is up to the task.

name: FieldSense
businessDescription:
Today, farming has gone digital. Farmers are surrounded by data from a variety of sources, utilizing this data effectively can have a massive positive impact on farmers everyday life. One thing that also massively impacts farmers everyday life is the weather. It impacts everything from harvesting to fertilising, to animal management and everything in between. 

Founded in 2015, FieldSense launched its agtech weather services in 2018. The startup provides hyper-local weather information and forecasts to help farmers monitor and act upon changes in local, microclimatic conditions. Based on weather data from in-field, solar-powered weather stations, the Danish agtech company creates user-friendly tools for farmers to help them in various important decisions. The FieldSense weather station is tailored for agro-purposes, accompanied by a farming-oriented and intuitive app. 

Every day, FieldSense collects more than 2 million weather measurements from close to 16.000 sensors that farmers can use in their day-to-day planning and operations –  a real game-changer for the industry.

name: MONEYBANKER
businessDescription: MONEYBANKER est un comparateur de crédits à la consommation. Notre plateforme comparative donne un aperçu direct sur les différentes offres de crédit proposées par les organismes. Un outil simple, rapide et efficace pour vous aider un trouver une aide de financement dans les meilleures conditions.
longBusinessDescription:
MONEYBANKER est une société danoise. La société fut fondée en 2015 par les deux entrepreneurs Mads Hvidberg et Simon Juhl. Forte de son succès, l'activité de la société s'est, aujourd'hui, étendue au marché finlandais, français, norvégien et américain. C'est, maintenant, sur le marché suédois que nous espérons étendre notre activité.
Nous travaillons, actuellement, sur la consolidation de notre marque sur les marchés sur lesquels nous sommes déjà présents. Pour cela, une équipe motivée, impliquée, mais aussi toujours de bonne humeur est dédiée, chaque jour, au développement de MONEYBANKER.
Comment nous différencions-nous de nos concurrents? La réponse est simple, nous nous différencions par la simplicité et la transparence de nos services. En effet, pour avoir un aperçu des offres disponibles, nul besoin d'entrer de nombreuses informations comme vos revenus, vos charges, votre adresse mail, etc. A partir du moment où vous vous rendez sur notre site, un aperçu vous est proposé. Si vous souhaitez des résultats personnalisés à votre situation, entrez alors le montant que vous souhaitez emprunter, ainsi que votre âge. De plus, la liste que nous proposons est complète. Certains sites ne proposent que quelques organismes suite à une recherche personnalisée. Pourquoi ces organismes précisément? Par partenariat? C'est pourquoi, sur notre site, une liste complète apparaît.
Vous avez entrez le montant que vous souhaitez emprunter dans notre moteur? Le tour est joué! Il ne vous reste plus qu'à envoyer votre demande de prêt aux organismes que vous aurez sélectionné au préalable en cliquant sur "simuler".
Nous nous considérons comme l'intermédiaire entre le futur emprunteur et l'organisme de crédit. En vous rendant sur notre site, le client a la garantie du sérieux des organismes comparés, ainsi que d'obtenir un aperçu complet des disponibilités du marché, lui évitant, ainsi, de passer à côté de l'offre la plus avantageuse.

name: Lift Relations
businessDescription:

name: OpenLedger ApS
businessDescription:
BUSINESS MADE SIMPLE WITH VIMPLE

Existing blockchain projects provide the user with no guarantee of network stability and offer no protection of legal rights.

The decision: to develop a legal blockchain created from the ground up for enterprise needs, enabling businesses to leverage all the advantages of peer-to-peer tools and services in organising their processes with domestic and global counterparts.
longBusinessDescription:
VPLedger blockchain ecosystem - Enterprise first, on every level
Existing blockchain projects provide the user with no guarantees of network stability and offer no
protection of legal rights. Businesses have therefore lacked the practical and legal reassurances they
need to leverage the considerable advantages of blockchain technology.
VPLedger is built from the ground up for enterprise needs, enabling businesses to integrate powerful
peer-to-peer tools and services into their processes within a clear legal framework.
Vision
VPLedger was created to offer businesses the
benefits of blockchain technology and
peer-to-peer financial operations, within a
stable, reliable technical framework and with
the legal and regulatory guarantees that
have previously been absent in the sector.
VPLedger’s ‘enterprise first’ ethos is evidenced
in a number of key features:
● High transaction throughput, suited for the
needs of global business.
● Suite of powerful tools and services,
including smart contracts, a decentralised
exchange, token creation, stablecoins and
other digital assets.
● Mandatory KYC for all users.
● Permissioned network with known
validating nodes, verified through
enhanced KYC.
● ‘Protective democracy’ approach, founded
on a Constitution.
● Clear legal framework for redress in the
event of fraudulent transactions.
VPLedger addresses both the technical and
regulatory shortcomings of earlier blockchains
and decentralised platforms, which have thus far
discouraged businesses from integrating these
new technologies into their processes.
The result is an ecosystem of decentralised
products and services, open to all but
accessible only by individuals and entities
willing to undergo identity verification. Within
this blockchain network, users are free to
undertake any activity they wish, subject to the
regulation in the relevant jurisdiction.
Technical approach
VPLedger is built on Graphene 3.0 , the
technology underpinning the BitShares
network. The use of a permissioned ledger
with a limited number of known, approved
validating nodes enables throughput of 100,000
transactions per second . Consensus is
achieved via the VPG algorithm.
The platform hosts a virtual machine, running
Ethereum-based smart contracts and
decentralised applications (dApps), enabling
businesses to execute complex logic in a
trustless environment.
The native currency and default means of
payment within the VPLedger ecosystem is
Vimples (VPL) : a unified, frictionless currency
for a global single market of blockchain
products and services. Unlike conventional
open blockchains, the task of securing the
network and processing transactions is
separated out from the payment layer; Vimples
are designed to function solely as a means of
accessing software services , rather than as a
speculative asset.
Meanwhile, a separate Governance body ,
consisting of users, will make democratic
decisions about the future technical and
economic directions of development and
activity for the network. This hybrid approach
allows VPLedger to offer a truly ‘enterprise first’
blockchain solution.
Key tools and technical functionality:
● Smart contracts and dApps
● Smartcoins, stablecoins and user assets
● Hierarchical account management system
● Automatic generation of business reports
● Cross-chain operations
● Transparency of team identity and funding
● Decentralised development
● Decentralised multi-wallet
● Block explorer and other blockchain tools
Key ecosystem features:
● Ability to interact with counterparties within
an enforceable legal framework
● Secure, reliable and transparent DLT
● Private transactions
● Up to 100,000 operations per second
● Transaction fees as low as 0.01%
● Free user-to-user transfers and messaging
● Opportunity to influence core economic
decisions and network characteristics
● Sophisticated tools for minimising financial
and counterparty risks
● Ability to work with both fiat and digital
currencies and assets
● Decentralised model of development and
improvement of blockchain protocol
● Well-developed, diverse ecosystem of
services
● Instant response to hacking and malicious
activity against network users via legal
instruments and recourse
● Multi-level user protections to facilitate
effective business operations
Business
VPLedger is designed for the needs of the $21
trillion global SME market.
All platform revenues are collected by
OpenLedger ApS, the technical developer of
VPLedger, to be distributed to stakeholders at
regular intervals. OpenLedger’s chief revenue
stream comes from Vimples purchased as part
of initial platform access, memberships and
top-ups. Vimples can be be purchased against
different currencies and on different AppStores
and e-commerce sites outside of the VPLedger
platform.
Users who purchase membership enjoy
benefits including 60% cashback on all
transactions, plus passive income from referred
users. Lifetime membership is available only
until January 2020. Revenues from transaction
fees will be shared among platform
stakeholders, including members , the
Governance body and validating nodes .
Up to 200 million Vimples will be sold by
OpenLedger ApS. After this, Governance will
decide whether OpenLedger will continue as
corporate head on a branch model, or hand
over the network to a Foundation. A further 10
billion VPL will fund platform marketing and
development.
Constitution
VPLedger is run on the model of a protective
democracy, according to a Constitution.
Validating nodes agree to adhere to the
Constitution. Thus fraud can be addressed
swiftly, but user rights and protections are
maintained and transactions cannot be blocked
or reversed without an appropriate legal order
by the relevant authorities
Team
VPLedger’s CEO is Ronny Boesing, founder of
OpenLedger ApS, the core developer for the
platform. Detailed information about the
activities of the VPLedger team, including the
history of all changes within the blockchain,
current work to improve the platform, the
results of referendums, etc, is all transparently
accessible and constantly updated on the
official VPLedger website.
Conclusion
VPLedger combines the best features of peer-to-peer technology within a legally compliant framework,
offering a bridge between fiat and the blockchain world. This enables businesses to leverage the benefits
of blockchain technology without the regulatory uncertainty that has prevented widespread adoption.
VPLedger is based on the principles of protective democracy, where economic decisions are made
directly by the users themselves. The blockchain is developed and maintained by the legal entity of
OpenLedger ApS, which is responsible for all the obligations undertaken under the VPLedger blockchain
Constitution.

name: WakeupData
businessDescription: WakeupData empowers e-commerce business by allowing you to combine and merge any data set with your product data feed, so businesses can optimize it and send it on to any given price comparison portal, marketplace or affiliate marketing platforms, saving you time and resources.
longBusinessDescription:
WakeupData ApS is an IT startup from Aarhus, founded in 2014. It was created in order to provide online stores with the maximum amount of high quality data feed integrations for the best value possible. We are based in Denmark, but we have a global soul. Our award winning team consists of eight different nationalities - a mere representation of the international landscape of Aarhus.
While being one of the six finalists at IBM's Business Connect 2015, WakeupData ApS proudly raised just above four million krones for future development efforts from initiatives such as Markedsmodningsfonden, Vækstfonden and the Innovationsfonden.
We are a member of FDIH, the Association of Danish E-commerce, and received the second place award in 2017 in the best e-commerce solution category for our work with Kaufmann.
In 2018 we achieved bronze in the 'Best E-commerce Tool in Denmark' category. We are continuously looking to grow our strategic partnership network through marketing & sales channels and agencies.
Our mission
We help online businesses automate and optimize their processes through high-quality data integrations, maximizing return on investment without the need for developers.
Our vision
Our vision is to become a leading platform for online businesses to manage, transform and enrich ANY dataset, giving them the best value by developing better interaction methods and new technologies for providing profitable data integration solutions.
Our value proposition
We offer a user-friendly interface to online stores and media agencies for transferring their correct and up-to-date data to countless platforms, with the help of our dedicated customer success managers.
Compared to other feed tool providers, we take a personal approach to each piece of data and deliver it to the right channel in a seamless way, focusing on the rules and best practices in each industry while shaping the content in the best way possible.
We want all our customers data to be secure, which is why we are cloud based, so that all users have a continuous and safe service at all times.
Our Why
WakeupData was born to simplify the work of thousands of people, whether you are an online business owner trying to increase your sales, a marketer trying to come up with a new way to market products or a PPC manager trying to help your clients to get the CPC down.
We’ve designed WakeupData to give you back the most precious currency: TIME. That is our North Star.
Our How
WakeupData technology has been developed to be a self-service tool for web shop owners, marketers and PPC managers, with that said, our internal motto is: 'We CARE about your business'.
Our dedicated Customer Success team builds strong relationships to make you and your company more profitable.
Our technology and our team will reduce your costs by advising you on best practices, including out-of-the-box solutions to standard and unforeseen challenges as well as incredibly fast implementations of data feed management solutions, so you can relax and get back precious time and resources.
Our What
Dennis Cassøe our co-founder had a vision.
After working in the core team that developed Wupti in 2013 he realised the need for a tool that could facilitate the integration of e-commerce platforms with EVERY channel.
Dennis felt the struggle of webshop owners and marketers to deliver quality data to each one of the thousands of sales channels, marketplaces and shopping carts in the global market.
Dennis created WakeupData to transform an incredibly complex problem shared by many, into an tool that is simple, easy to use and a fraction of the cost of other solutions and which generates ROI within 14 days.

name: EasySize
businessDescription:
EasySize is a data-driven technology defining clothes sizes and decreasing returns at online-shops. We help online-shops to save money and offer their clients a new shopping experience.
EasySize can be integrated to an online-shop in less than an hour using our API literally by copy-pasting a snippet of code and apps for popular platforms (Magento, Shopify, Opencart, Prestashop). Our technology analyses a given customers order records and defines a desired brand's size in less than a second.
For a new online-shop customer, the only thing we ask is to add any known brand size. And for a returning online-shop customer, EasySize can define the size by analysing previous order records and show it on every open page - so the customer shouldn't do anything at all.
EasySize can decrease returns by 35-40% and save up to 5-7% of revenue to online-shops.

TECHNOLOGY

EasySize is built on a technology analysing online-shops orders records. It means that the size is calculated not based on what clients think they look like or prefer to think they look like, but on a hard data - what they actually buy, return and do not return.
The core algorithm uses various factors from manufacturing country to clothes cut and fabric in order to define the correct size. Using a machine learning it can dynamically in real time update results and becomes smarter every time an order is made on an online-shop.
During tests with real online-shops in Europe EasySize predicted the correct size which customers did not return in 79,45% of all cases.
Our API allows integrate EasySize in less than an hour and doesn't require any specific information or actions from an online-shop.

longBusinessDescription:
Monsenso
Monsenso is an innovative technology company offering an mHealth solution for mental health.
Our mission is to help clinicians, researchers, and individuals overcome the burden of mental illness.
The Monsenso mHealth solution can help in the prevention, early intervention and treatment of mental or behavioural disorders by providing a detailed overview of a patients mental health through the collection of behavioural data and self-monitoring.
Connecting individuals, carers and clinicians
Individuals use a smartphone app to fill in their self-assessments and clinical questionnaires. Additionally, the smartphone also collects sensor data, such as physical activity, mobility and phone usage.
Carers use a similar app which allows them to play a more active role in the treatment of the one they care for, while obtaining the information they need. With the smartphone app, carers can make notes that are shared with both individuals and clinicians.
Clinicians can access the information collected by the users and carers smartphones. The clinical web portal provides them with an overview of the individuals historical data, symptoms, medication compliance, triggers, and warning signs.

Our vision is to be the leading collaborative End-of-Arm Tooling company and offer our customers innovative collaborative solutions with true Plug & Play functionality.

name: Be My Eyes
businessDescription: Be My Eyes is a free mobile app designed to bring sight to the blind and visually impaired. With the press of a button, the app establishes a live video connection between blind and visually impaired users and sighted volunteers and company representatives. With over 2.2 million users across 150 countries, Be My Eyes has grown to become the largest online community for the blind and visually impaired. Be My Eyes work with companies like Microsoft and Google who offer accessible customer support through Be My Eyes'​ Specialized Help. The app harnesses the power of generosity, technology and human connection to help blind and visually impaired individuals lead more independent lives.
tags: eHealth, Accessibility, Disabilities, Healthcare, BeMyEyes, Denmark

name: Labster
businessDescription:
Labster is an internationally focused company dedicated to the development of pioneering online tools for teaching science globally. Our primary product is an easily scalable online platform for teaching biotechnology that has been demonstrated to improve learning significantly over standard methods as well as substantially reduce costs.
Labsters business is dedicated to bringing life science teaching to life. We think every day about the big picture of science education. The Labster platform is a 3D virtual learning environment based on a Virtual Lab.

name: Babyandi.dk
businessDescription:
Baby&I er en online webshop, hvor du kan finde alt, hvad du behøver i din hverdag med en lille på armen. Bag Baby&I finder du Betina og Michael Duve, der sammen har tre børn og dermed kender til livet med små børn i hjemmet og de særlige behov en baby i hjemmet giver. I webshoppen har de derfor skabt et stort univers, der byder på alt, hvad du har brug for til din nyfødte baby - og alt hvad du som forælder har brug for, for at give dit barn en god start på livet.

I det store sortiment kan du finde sødt tøj til den lille, alt til pusletimen og en masse legetøj der indbyder til hyggelige aktiviteter. Hos Baby&I udvider de hele tiden deres sortiment for at imødekomme de ønsker, I som forældre har rapid hver gang du går på opdagelse på webshoppen vil du derfor kunne finde endnu flere produkter fra anerkendte producenter.

Sortimentet er altid udvalgt med omtanke. Alle produkter er derfor i god kvalitet og lækre materialer og derudover til en konkurrencedygtig pris. Desuden udvælger de deres produkter ud fra deres opfattelse af, at selvom livet med en baby er praktisk, må tøj, legetøj og pusleting gerne være lækkert instructions og det er synligt i deres udvalg.

Gå på opdagelse på Baby&I allerede nu, og find alt til dig og din lille. Vil du gerne i kontakt med baby&I kan det gøres på telefon 71 70 07 76 eller på mail til [email protected].

name: Sneuniverset
businessDescription: Sneuniverset er en blog omhandlende - sne! Bloggen drives af snerydningsfirmaet snevagten.dk, som er et af Danmarks førende indenfor denne branche.
tags: Broadcast Media, Winter News, Video Blog
longBusinessDescription:
Sneuniverset er en videoblog, der omhandler sne hele året rundt. Videobloggen hører under Snevagten A/S, der er ejet af Christoffer Gade. Sneuniverset beskæftiger sig med sne sommer og vinter, og via videoindlæggene får du således indsigt i hvordan det er at drive et snerydningsfirma.
Vi udgiver en ny videoepisode hver uge. Vi ved godt, at det kun sner 2-3 måneder om året, men vi er forberedte alle årets 365 dage.
Når du har besøgt vores blog, får du måske lyst til at kontakte Snevagten for at starte et samarbejde om din eller din virksomheds snerydning. Hos Snevagten A/S tilbyder vi professionel saltning og snerydning, og du kan til hver en tid ringe på 38 71 17 00 for et modtage et uforpligtende tilbud.
Vi tilbyder snerydning i hele Danmark, både i Hovedstaden, på Fyn, i Jylland og på Bornholm. Ring til os når du har brug for en professionel samarbejdspartner til snerydning, og hold dig opdateret på Christoffer Gades gøren og laden på videbloggen, Sneuniverset.dk, alle årets 365 dage.

name: InfluAds
businessDescription: The advertising network InfluAds, which is based in Copenhagen, was founded on February of 2010 by Anibal Damião. InfluAds allows publishers to team up with other publishers and develop carefully curated ad networks around their passion, focusing on quality through a minimalist ad presence.

name: Ge.tt
businessDescription: Ge.tt was founded in October 2010 and aims to become the easiest-to-use file-transfer service in the world. Rather than e-mail files, which can be difficult with large files, users can use Ge.tt to store and transfer them easily to as many recipients as they choose. Ge.tt also provides users with a nice stepping stone to the benefits of cloud computing. Files can be downloaded while they are being uploaded, users are able to easily copy a link to the file, or send as e-mail directly from Ge.tt. And there is no requirement to sign up or install any software, making it as simple and as fast as possible.
tags: Files Transfer Tool, Big Files, Social Media

name: Digizuite
businessDescription: Digizuite Digital Asset Management software for enterprises. Take control of your digital content. Search, manage, and share and repurpose files from one source.
tags: Asset Management, Digital Media, Permision Control
longBusinessDescription:
Digizuite Media Manager is a highly secure digital asset management system, designed to ensure your digital assets are safe and protected using an enhanced access and permission control. You define media management and access rights to your digital assets based on individual users, groups or roles. These rights management processes can also be connected with other systems through AD sync.
This ensures that the right people have access to the right content when they need it, from whatever device they are using. And you remain in full control of your digital information  and your brand.
